<header id="nodeDecoration"><h1 id="nodeTitle">10  PROJECT OVERSIGHT</h1></header>
<article class="iDevice_wrapper FreeTextIdevice" id="id41">
<div class="iDevice emphasis0">
<div id="ta41_85" class="block iDevice_content">
<table width="100%" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0">
<tbody>
<tr>
<td width="3%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">10 </span></span></p>
</td>
<td colspan="2" width="97%">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="6" style="font-size: xx-large;"><b>PROJECT OVERSIGHT</b></span></span></p>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>Describe the oversight practices that provide sufficient knowledge of all grant activities to ensure proper and efficient administration of the project. </b></span></span></p>
<ol type="a">
<li>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>Identify the Project Director and Co-Project Director.</b></span></span></p>
</li>
<li>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>List oversight practices and activities.</b></span></span></p>
</li>
</ol>
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;"><b>Project Directors, Co-Project Directors, and any collaborators who will receive a portion of the project funds must provide whichever is most applicable - either a current Resume or Curriculum Vitae (CV). <br /> <br /> Attach Resumes or CVs in PDF format and name each document: R1, R2, R3 or CV1, CV2, CV3, etc. <br /> <br /> If applicable, are Resumes and/or CVs attached? </b></span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="3%">
<p class="western"> </p>
</td>
<td width="12%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Answer: </span></span></p>
</td>
<td width="85%">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">l YES </span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="3%">
<p class="western"> </p>
</td>
<td width="12%" valign="top">
<p class="western" align="right"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">Answer: </span></span></p>
</td>
<td width="85%" valign="top">
<p class="western"><span face="Times New Roman, serif" style="font-family: 'Times New Roman', serif;"><span size="3" style="font-size: medium;">a. Project Director: Dr. Michel McLaughlin, WE CAN Foundation. Dr. McLaughlin has been director of WE CAN Foundation for 17 years and has administered the Foundations $1.3 million annual budget relative to California DOE Supplemental Educational Services.<br /> b. Oversight practices and activities:<br /> 1. Financial accounting: Maintain full program budgets that account for all program expenses, indicating identity of all recipients and how money is used.<br /> 2. Banking: Establish separate bank account for independent administration of grant funds<br /> 3. Program verifications: Maintain full records regarding program attendance and participation at all activities, including:<br /> -Descriptions of all project activities carried out<br /> -Listing of all beneficiaries of each aspect of project<br /> -Tracking of all program events and activities<br /> -Accounting of all funds, UF installations and assets<br /> -Tracking of all produce harvested<br /> -Tracking of all sales of produce<br /> -Regular direct field audits of all program sites </span></span></p>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>
